ğŸ” Your job: After gaining a foothold, dig everywhere for creds that help escalate or pivot. Think: Where would a human screw up and leave sensitive info laying around?
The goal? Admin creds, password reuse, SSH keys, service creds, or escalation paths.

ğŸ§­ CATEGORIES TO HUNT
Think in 4 core buckets â€” files, memory, history, and system configs:

Category	Examples
ğŸ—‚ï¸ Files	Configs, scripts, databases, SSH keys
ğŸ§  Memory	Running processes, keyrings, Mimipenguin
ğŸ•“ History	.bash_history, .bashrc, command logs
ğŸ§¾ Logs	/var/log/*, cron logs, auth logs
ğŸ”½ FILES â€“ THE LOW-HANGING FRUIT
ğŸ”§ Config Files (likely to contain creds)
